# Shadcn-UI Migration Guide

## **Overview**

This guide shows how to migrate from hardcoded TailwindCSS classes to our Shadcn-UI style ViewComponents, making the codebase more maintainable and consistent.

## **🔄 Component Migration Patterns**

### **1. Card Components**

**❌ Before (Hardcoded)**
```erb
<div class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4 shadow-sm">
  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Account Summary</h3>
  <p class="text-gray-600">Your account balance and recent activity.</p>
  <div class="mt-4 pt-4 border-t border-gray-200">
    <button class="bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md">View Details</button>
  </div>
</div>
```

**✅ After (Component)**
```erb
<%= render DS::Card.new do |card| %>
  <% card.with_header(title: "Account Summary") %>
  <% card.with_body do %>
    Your account balance and recent activity.
  <% end %>
  <% card.with_footer do %>
    <%= render DS::Button.new(variant: "primary", text: "View Details") %>
  <% end %>
<% end %>
```

### **2. Status Badges**

**❌ Before (Hardcoded)**
```erb
<span class="inline-flex items-center px-2 py-1 text-xs font-medium bg-green-100 text-green-800 rounded-md">
  Active
</span>
<span class="inline-flex items-center px-2 py-1 text-xs font-medium bg-red-100 text-red-800 rounded-md">
  Error
</span>
```

**✅ After (Component)**
```erb
<%= render DS::Badge.new(variant: "success", text: "Active", icon: "check") %>
<%= render DS::Badge.new(variant: "destructive", text: "Error", icon: "x") %>
```

### **3. Button Groups**

**❌ Before (Hardcoded)**
```erb
<div class="flex gap-2">
  <button class="bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-blue-700">
    Save
  </button>
  <button class="border border-gray-300 bg-white text-gray-700 px-4 py-2 rounded-md hover:bg-gray-50">
    Cancel
  </button>
</div>
```

**✅ After (Component)**
```erb
<div class="flex gap-2">
  <%= render DS::Button.new(variant: "primary", text: "Save") %>
  <%= render DS::Button.new(variant: "outline", text: "Cancel") %>
</div>
```

### **4. Form Inputs (Future Implementation)**

**❌ Before (Hardcoded)**
```erb
<div class="space-y-2">
  <label class="block text-sm font-medium text-gray-700">Email</label>
  <input type="email" class="w-full px-3 py-2 border border-gray-300 rounded-md focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500">
  <p class="text-sm text-red-600">Please enter a valid email</p>
</div>
```

**✅ After (Component - To Be Implemented)**
```erb
<%= render DS::Input.new(
  type: "email",
  label: "Email",
  error: "Please enter a valid email",
  variant: "error"
) %>
```

## **🎯 Migration Strategy**

### **Phase 1: High-Impact Components**

1. **Identify repetitive patterns** in views
2. **Convert to DS components** starting with most used patterns
3. **Update design tokens** to use functional classes

### **Phase 2: Form Components**

1. **Implement DS::Input, DS::Select, DS::Checkbox**
2. **Create form builder integration**
3. **Migrate form views**

### **Phase 3: Layout Components**

1. **Implement DS::Sheet, DS::Popover**
2. **Create layout helpers**
3. **Migrate complex layouts**

## **🔍 Finding Migration Candidates**

### **Search Patterns**

```bash
# Find hardcoded card patterns
grep -r "bg-white.*border.*rounded" app/views/

# Find hardcoded button patterns
grep -r "bg-blue-.*text-white.*px-.*py-" app/views/

# Find hardcoded badge patterns
grep -r "inline-flex.*px-.*py-.*text-xs" app/views/
```

### **Common Anti-Patterns**

```erb
<!-- ❌ Hardcoded colors -->
<div class="bg-blue-600 text-white">

<!-- ✅ Design tokens -->
<div class="bg-primary text-inverse">

<!-- ❌ Hardcoded spacing -->
<div class="px-4 py-2 mt-3">

<!-- ✅ Component variants -->
<%= render DS::Card.new(size: "md") %>
```

## **🧪 Testing Migration**

### **Visual Regression Testing**

```ruby
# Before migration - capture screenshots
rails test:system

# After migration - compare
rails test:system
```

### **Component Testing**

```ruby
class DS::CardTest < ViewComponent::TestCase
  def test_renders_with_all_slots
    render_inline DS::Card.new do |card|
      card.with_header(title: "Test")
      card.with_body { "Content" }
      card.with_footer { "Footer" }
    end
    
    assert_selector "header", text: "Test"
    assert_selector "div", text: "Content"
    assert_selector "footer", text: "Footer"
  end
end
```

