## **🎯 Benefits After Migration**

1. **Consistency** - All components follow same patterns
2. **Maintainability** - Changes in one place affect all instances
3. **Accessibility** - Built-in ARIA attributes and semantic HTML
4. **Performance** - Smaller CSS bundle, better caching
5. **Developer Experience** - IntelliSense, type safety, previews
6. **Design System** - Clear component hierarchy and variants

## **⚠️ Common Pitfalls**

1. **Don't migrate everything at once** - Do it incrementally
2. **Don't break existing functionality** - Test thoroughly
3. **Don't ignore edge cases** - Handle custom styling needs
4. **Don't forget documentation** - Update as you go
5. **Don't skip testing** - Both unit and visual tests

This migration approach ensures we get all the benefits of Shadcn-UI patterns while maintaining our HTML-over-JavaScript architecture and Rails conventions.